    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-03T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-03T05:00:00-05:00" n="232"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d232">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/2459: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cole</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-03T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 3, 1941—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 3—10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>112. Leading military economic source states gasoline vitally important
                    militarily for Africa. Army now using reserves thus reducing chances successful
                    defense.</p>
                <p>Civil sources state propaganda value ship load hard wheat destined free
                    distribution natives only would be enormous. Points out natives losing faith
                    England after Nemours.<note n="10" xml:id="d232fn10">Anglo-French naval incident
                        between Nemours and Oran, March 30, 1940.</note> United States would serve
                    as bridge. Suggested importation low priced receiving sets capable getting
                    United States. Believe both last suggestions worth study.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cole</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
